    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add your <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and<strong> basmati rice</strong> and stir to fully coat the grains</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>nigella rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely (set aside some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>sultanas</strong> and <strong>mango chutney</strong> to the stock and stir to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>mango stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, then increase the heat to medium-high and cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, a good grind of<strong> pepper</strong> and the<strong> drained chickpeas</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 2-3 min or until everything is coated in the spices</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>mango</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and <strong>chopped green beans</strong> and cook for a further 5-6 min or until the stock has reduced by half</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir in your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Taste and season with more<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed \u2013 this is your <strong>coronation chickpea curry</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>nigella rice</strong> with a fork</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coronation-chickpea-curry-with-nigella-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>coronation chickpea curry</strong> over the <strong>nigella rice</strong> and garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
